    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-08T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-08T02:00:00-05:00" n="466"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d466">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11708: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow (<persName
                            corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1" type="from">Adams</persName>) to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-08T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 8, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. <hi rend="italic">Oahu</hi> reports that the Standard Oil Company’s motor
                    vessel <hi rend="italic">Meishan</hi>, under the control of a Chinese <hi
                        rend="italic">laodah</hi>, looted today by 20 bandits at mileage 119 above
                    Hankow. The loss was slight excepting that one package of mail and the ship’s
                    papers were taken by the bandits. The <hi rend="italic">Meishan</hi> is now
                    anchored near the <hi rend="italic">Oahu.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Legation informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_AWA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Adams</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
